Running command: cat > /workspace/reproduce_issue.py << 'PY'
from django.db.models.sql.query import Query
from django.db.models.sql.datastructures import BaseTable

# Construct a Query object without a full model. We only need alias_map and related
q = Query(model=None)
# Prepare alias_map with two aliases that would conflict in a chained rename
q.alias_map = {
    'T4': BaseTable('foo_table', 'T4'),
    'T5': BaseTable('bar_table', 'T5'),
}
q.alias_refcount = {'T4': 1, 'T5': 1}
q.table_map = {'foo_table': ['T4'], 'bar_table': ['T5']}
q.external_aliases = {}

change_map = {'T4': 'T5', 'T5': 'T6'}

print('Before change:', list(q.alias_map.keys()))
q.change_aliases(change_map)
print('After change:', list(q.alias_map.keys()))

# Verify final aliases present
assert 'T6' in q.alias_map
print('Change aliases succeeded')
PY
